# BRAIN — local operational state (manifest, memories, audit ledger, lock file).
# Deliberately gitignored: the BRAIN holds tenant-specific data that doesn't
# belong in version control (per AGENTS.md §0.1 and the user's explicit
# decision on 2026-05-11). The reference writer that mutates the BRAIN lives
# at runtime/lib/brain_writer.py and IS tracked in git, so the protocol's
# implementation surface ships with the repo even though the BRAIN itself
# does not. Backup the BRAIN out-of-band (memory-export-<DATE>-<scope>.zip).
# As of the .cyberos/ unification (§0.4), the BRAIN store lives at .cyberos/memory/store/.
.cyberos/

# CUO workflow activity history (step JSON cache, ADRs, audits, impl plans,
# code reviews, obs injections) — lives in .cyberos/memory/store/ subdirectories,
# not in docs/. Covered by the .cyberos/memory/store gitignore above.

# Aspect 13.5 audit (2026-05-12) — transient build/cache, editor junk, local analytics
.DS_Store

# Python build / cache
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# Generated state now lives inside the BRAIN (Batch 27 reorg, 2026-05-12).
# The BRAIN itself (.cyberos/memory/store) is already gitignored above, which covers
# .cyberos/memory/store/cache/*, .cyberos/memory/store/staging/*, and .cyberos/memory/store/refinements/*.
# No separate var/ folder anymore — generated artefacts are regenerable to
# .cyberos/memory/store/cache/<tool>/ on demand. Single source of state truth = BRAIN.

# Editor / OS junk
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/extensions.json

# Rust / Cargo build output (large, regenerable)
target/
**/target/

# Transient commit-message scratch files (created mid-session, deleted after commit)
.commit-msg-*.txt

# Node / JS deps + build output
node_modules/
dist/
.next/
.nuxt/

# Secrets — defense-in-depth (denylist §9.3 also catches them)
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
# Deploy env templates are placeholders only (no secrets) — keep them tracked.
!.env.p0.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
.protocol-signing-key
# Live token / credential material (e.g. deploy/obs/auth/*.live). Never commit.
*.live
*.token.live
deploy/**/*.live

# Test artifacts
.coverage
htmlcov/
*.cover
# proptest saves failing-case regression files; they are large and machine-local.
*.proptest-regressions
**/*.proptest-regressions
website/docs/.wrangler/

# Build report artifacts (ephemeral, regenerated by build.sh)
website/build/last-*-report.json

# Cargo build artefacts (per repo-layout-doctrine in README — services/ is a workspace)
services/target/

# Workbench consume 2026-05-19 — the workbench/ folder was absorbed into
# playground/ flat. Its CyberSkill-authored content (CYBEROS_STRATEGY.md,
# CyberOS-docs/, cyberos-*.md notes, cyberos-memory-workbench-archive/) is
# tracked; the 10 cloned upstream reference repos are NOT — they have their
# own .git histories and would bloat cyberos commits. They live on disk for
# browsing, but stay out of git. See playground/CONSUMED-FROM-WORKBENCH.md.
playground
.claude/

# Signed employment contracts - kept out of version control (cited by clause number in the EVAL rubric)
docs/legal/*.docx

# tool caches (never committed)
.code-review-graph/
.remember/

# Vercel (docs hosting) build staging
.vercel-out/
.vercel

# generated docs site shipped to the VPS by deploy.yml (job: docs) - never committed
apps/console/docs/

# Android signing keystore - PRIVATE KEY, never commit (base64 it into a GitHub secret instead)
release.keystore
*.keystore
*.jks
*.p8
*.mobileprovision
*.cer
*.certSigningRequest
